properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 3 at 2:15PM PST until February 5 at 7:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the first Small Craft Advisory, seas 9 to 12 feet
at 12 seconds. For the second Small Craft Advisory, southwest
winds 20 to 30 kt and seas 12 to 17 feet at 18 seconds.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters from Cape Flattery to Cape Shoalwater
out to 60 nm.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 10 PM PST this
evening. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 7 AM Tuesday to 7
AM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 21 to 33 knots
and/or seas 10 feet or higher are expected to produce hazardous
wave conditions to small craft. Inexperienced mariners,
especially those operating smaller vessels should avoid
navigating in these conditions.
